Winning the war within 💪🏼

I started working out with @taylormadetraining 4 years ago, but l fell off during the pandemic. 😏 I’ve tried a lot of other workouts, but I struggle with self motivation, so I really needed the accountability that comes with a trainer 🫡. I resumed working out with Taylor 6 months ago and I’ve been back on track with my workouts! Now my goal is to stick with my 2023 routine which is 3 HIIT x week and 3 5k’s x week for cardio! 

Doing too much at all times triggers my anxiety but every workout elevates my mood, I can literally feel the cortisol leaving my body and the serotonin getting to work! 🧘🏼‍♀️

Get in a workout = get instant gratification!
Thanks for coming to my tedtalk 🙃

Oxtails at #KarensKitchen 👩🏻‍🍳!

Sundays are usually reserved for soul food at Karen’s Kitchen. Tonight I whipped up braised oxtails in the dutch oven. These braised oxtail have all the components of a Caribbean oxtail minus the butter beans & carrots, and as you can see I also did a wine braise 🍷 , leftover wine does just the trick! The beauty about braising is you can make it your own, but @myforkinglife’s recipe inspired me tonight. 
Oxtails are from @lamichoacanamm 
Everything else is from @heb 🛒 

Sounds by the talented 🎻 @dominiquehammonsviolin 

Now, I’m ready for all the Grammy performances!

Y’all are in line for Beyoncé tickets, I’m in line at the grand opening of @thesmokehtx 💨 . We are not the same! 🤪

Seriously, no shade for Bey fans, I’m just eager to share the news 🗞. The Smoke 💨 , chef Reggie’s (@bestdamn_everything) BBQ restaurant is officially open for business! I met chef at the Oxtail Mash Up and I knew right away that he was a force to be reckoned with. Now he’s evolving from his well known BBQ cart to this brick & mortar outpost at @finnhall! The hall itself has been reimagined with lots of dining options and a premium bar pouting some amazingly crafted cocktails and local brews 🍺, by @swallowsnesthtx! 

Now let’s talk about the food! Y’all I had the best brisket baked potato I’ve ever had in my life! FR! 
The tender brisket, smoked chicken boudain (I love boudain - so the chicken is a welcome variety) and smoked wings are also a highlight of the menu. Chef Reggie finished his dishes with “smoke dust”, which is his signature proprietary blend of spices that is just chefs kiss 🤌🏼! Everything is so amazing and I’m counting down the days until I go back! The Smoke HTX is now open daily. Follow them and save this post to visit them 🔜 
. 

Ty for the invite 🥰 @rashadeatstheworld 
.

In the voice of Miley Cyrus: “I can buy myself cocktails”

Margaritas to be more specific 🤪 and specially today because they’re $5 at @latinbiteskitchen for National Margarita day.

Pictured however is a premium Rita called La Patrona which is a passion fruit rita 🍹 or as I know it, #maracuya.

I’ve been diagnosed with O.C.D. “Obsessive Crawfish Disorder”. 🤪

I don’t know the side effects but I’m eating crawfish at least twice a week 😂. One of my favorite crawfish boils during the season is the Mambo style crawfish at @mamboseafood 🦞 

Mambo Style Crawfish consists of visible garlic bits 🧄 , light on butter 🧈 , and heavy on citrus and flavor 🤤 ! Made with their blend of spices aka Mambo Style seasoning! 

This season they introduced a combo that features their Mambo Style Shrimp shrimp + crawfish! Its all you need to fill your crawfish cravings! That’s what I ordered and added 4 lbs. YES, I can put it down like that when it comes to crawfish, it’s part my OCD. 🤪

I also ordered the Mi Chelada Mambonifica! Which is a Mexican mango 🥭 michelada that’s dressed up like a Mexican Bloody Mary if you will! 😝 

Live Crawfish is available now at all 10 Houston area locations! Save this post for your next crawfish outing! 

Taking the party home 🏠? No problem! Order on their website for curbside pick-up! 

#mamboseafood a Houston tradition!
.
.

Blue Checkmarks for all ✔️😱?!

Our Founder/CEO @karendeamat, sat down with @isiahcareyfox26 on the @theisiahfactor to discuss the latest bombshell from Meta 📲. 

Facebook and Meta have added a new source of user gratification, while creating a new source of revenue, taking the lead from Twitter who rolled out their verification badge late last year. 

Introducing Meta Verified, users will soon be able to feel the gratification of having a verified badge on their page by simply paying a monthly subscription 💵 and verifying their identity. 

Karen comments on the recent economic downturn for the social tech giant, and why this is a move to procure subscription revenue to mitigate some recent losses, amidst the crisis in Silicon Valley.   

How do you feel about this update? And will you be subscribing? Weigh-in in the comments!

If you didn’t celebrate NATIONAL BBQ DAY today, fear not, everyday is BBQ day at @raysbbqshack 😎. 

BBQ is an everyday thing at Ray’s but this month is extra special because National BBQ month.

Their proprietary recipes and time-honored smoking techniques have been passed down from their Founder & Pitmaster, Rayford Busch. They’ve been smoking in Houston’s 3rd ward since 1984! It’s a Houston institution I wish I’d known about sooner (frfr!)

Start planning your visit and save these weekly features:

😋 Nacho average Tuesday, a play on #tacotuesday, are for Loaded BBQ Nachos. Choose from brisket or chicken topped with queso, guacamole, sour cream, & pico. 

😋 Every Thursday they smoke succulent fall off-the-bone oxtails! 

😋 Don’t pass on their homemade desserts and take a bottle of their Bomb BBQ Sauce home!

If you don’t want to venture out, you can find them on Uber Eats & DoorDash 💃!!! 

Follow @raysbbqshack as they close out BBQ month with some mouthwatering surprises & collaborations😉! 

📍3929 Old Spanish Trail ste. 300, 
Houston, TX 77021

Flavor of the motherland, el Sabor Peruano 🇵🇪🔥🤌🏽…

@chickhouz is my go-to for classic Peruvian rotisserie chicken 🍗! The flavor takes me straight home to my birthplace, Peru! 

Consider this our version of BBQ. Peruvian rotisserie starts with a in-house 24 hour marinade made with proprietary spices imported from Peru. Then charcoal grilled to perfection in an imported rotisserie oven. 😋

Rotisserie chicken is a staple food in Peru and it’s mainly served with fries, rice and salad! Chick Houz has expanded side options and a variety of sides! 

They have two Houston locations, Energy Corridor and Humble, TX. But don’t let distance deter you, they also serve their chicken at their sister restaurant @latinbiteskitchen in Tanglewood! 

This is a MUST-TRY so add it to your list when you want to savor the best Peruvian food in Houston! We order from here at least once a week on DoorDash or Uber.
